WEBVTT

00:00.725 --> 00:02.969
Hey, Mr. Shue, it's Rachel,
how are you?

00:03.020 --> 00:04.186
Rachel, hey, good.

00:04.221 --> 00:06.471
Yeah, just, uh, getting ready
for regionals.

00:06.523 --> 00:08.140
Well, I wanted you to be
the first that I told...

00:08.191 --> 00:10.643
even before Kurt, before
my dads, or even before Finn...

00:10.677 --> 00:13.312
that I had my callback
for <i>Funny Girl</i> this morning.

00:13.363 --> 00:14.614
Wait, did you get Fanny Brice?

00:14.648 --> 00:15.681
Not yet, but it's between me

00:15.716 --> 00:17.316
and two other girls.

00:17.367 --> 00:18.868
Oh, that is
incredible news, Rachel.

00:18.902 --> 00:20.119
Y-You're a shoo-in.

00:20.153 --> 00:22.738
Aw, I just want you to know
that if it does happen,

00:22.772 --> 00:23.956
it's because of you.

00:23.991 --> 00:26.325
Well, if, if I contributed
even a little bit...

00:26.376 --> 00:28.294
Well, you contributed
more than a little.

00:28.328 --> 00:31.080
I sang "Don't Stop Believin'"
for my audition,

00:31.114 --> 00:33.966
and when I sang it,
I thought about that first week

00:34.001 --> 00:35.751
that we were all in Glee Club

00:35.785 --> 00:37.553
and how amazing
we all were together,

00:37.588 --> 00:39.655
and it just brought back
so many emotions,

00:39.690 --> 00:42.341
it made my performance
so powerful,

00:42.392 --> 00:45.011
and, well, you were the one that
put that all together, so...

00:46.063 --> 00:47.980
You okay, Mr. Shue?

00:48.015 --> 00:49.815
Yeah, fine, just allergies.

00:53.020 --> 00:56.822
Rachel... I'm so proud of you.

00:56.857 --> 00:58.908
Y-You're one of our biggest
success stories,

00:58.942 --> 01:01.327
a-and no matter what happens
with <i>Funny Girl,</i>

01:01.361 --> 01:03.663
I mean, you're in New York,
you're living your dream.

01:03.697 --> 01:04.914
Not many people can say that.

01:04.947 --> 01:06.165
I know,

01:06.199 --> 01:10.369
it's a special
and wonderful thing, so...

01:10.420 --> 01:11.837
And when I'm at Radio City

01:11.872 --> 01:14.840
and I'm accepting my Tony Award
and I forget to thank you, well,

01:14.875 --> 01:16.342
thank you.

01:16.376 --> 01:17.510
Thank you.

01:21.598 --> 01:23.549
Wonderful.

01:23.600 --> 01:27.520
All right, guys, I just got
some wonderful news from Rachel.

01:27.554 --> 01:29.689
She's got a second callback
for <i>Funny Girl.</i>

01:32.059 --> 01:34.193
And that's not
our only good news.

01:34.227 --> 01:36.062
Brittany is at M.I.T.
touring the campus

01:36.113 --> 01:38.230
because she's got
an early acceptance.

01:38.281 --> 01:39.231
That can't be true.

01:39.282 --> 01:41.784
And I re-proposed
to Emma.

01:41.818 --> 01:44.370
She reaccepted, and we're
getting married after regionals.

01:44.404 --> 01:45.788
Yay!
We're excited.

01:47.074 --> 01:48.541
I've got good news, too.

01:48.575 --> 01:50.743
I'm wait-listed at the Columbus
College of Veterinary Medicine.

01:50.794 --> 01:52.461
It's a fallback
if I don't pursue acting.

01:52.496 --> 01:53.546
Bless her heart.

01:53.580 --> 01:55.214
Tina, that's
not just good news.

01:55.248 --> 01:56.916
It's wonderful,

01:56.967 --> 01:58.751
and that's what this
week is all about.

01:58.802 --> 02:01.003
We're taking a lesson from one
of the greatest musical artists

02:01.037 --> 02:02.221
of all time.

02:02.255 --> 02:04.473
Despite facing a ton of
obstacles,

02:04.508 --> 02:06.425
he's a living example
of embracing...

02:06.476 --> 02:09.895
n-n-no, <i>celebrating...</i>
joy and optimism,

02:09.930 --> 02:12.314
and he's collected
25 Grammys along the way.

02:12.349 --> 02:14.233
So don't you worry 'bout a thing

02:14.267 --> 02:16.102
