to me, too, are you?

35:57.229 --> 35:58.897
I just wanted to give you this.

35:58.948 --> 36:01.282
You can open it.

36:02.618 --> 36:05.236
I thought maybe you
could wear it at work

36:05.287 --> 36:06.687
to show support
for gay marriage.

36:06.705 --> 36:08.022
Oh, it's really sweet of you.

36:08.040 --> 36:10.191
Gay rights has been
my top issue,

36:10.209 --> 36:11.993
even though it makes me
wildly unpopular

36:12.027 --> 36:13.527
with my distinguished
colleagues.

36:13.546 --> 36:16.414
They're on the wrong side
of history, so screw 'em.

36:17.800 --> 36:20.585
I am so glad
that you feel that way,

36:20.636 --> 36:23.371
because assuming
that we legally can,

36:23.389 --> 36:26.925
um, I wanted to formally ask
for your permission

36:26.976 --> 36:29.093
to ask Kurt to marry me.

36:30.145 --> 36:32.647
You kidding, or you nuts?

36:34.650 --> 36:36.717
Kurt is my soul mate.

36:36.735 --> 36:38.770
I know that I've
hurt him badly,

36:38.821 --> 36:41.189
but I also know
that if I want to get him back,

36:41.223 --> 36:42.407
I have to do something bold.

36:42.441 --> 36:44.609
Blaine,

36:44.660 --> 36:46.778
it means a lot to me
that you love Kurt,

36:46.829 --> 36:50.114
and you know,
you've been like family to me...

36:50.165 --> 36:52.566
So, you' saying that you're okay

36:52.585 --> 36:54.419
with me asking for his hand?

36:54.453 --> 36:56.737
Oh, of course not.
No, you're still kids.

36:56.755 --> 36:59.424
Did you learn anything
from Finn and Rachel?

36:59.458 --> 37:01.125
They are completely different.

37:01.176 --> 37:02.460
Completely different.

37:02.511 --> 37:03.962
I don't think
that you understand

37:04.013 --> 37:05.296
how it feels

37:05.347 --> 37:08.249
to finally be able
to legally get married.

37:08.267 --> 37:12.470
And you don't really get
what it is to be married.

37:12.521 --> 37:14.422
Straight, gay, whatever.

37:14.440 --> 37:16.257
It's not the same
as living together.

37:16.275 --> 37:17.475
Blaine, listen,

37:17.526 --> 37:19.593
let's sit down for a second.

37:19.612 --> 37:21.613
Seriously, come here.

37:25.868 --> 37:28.820
Look, I can't tell you why,

37:28.871 --> 37:31.823
but something happens
when you exchange vows.

37:31.874 --> 37:34.492
It's a big deal.

37:34.543 --> 37:37.795
It's why getting divorce is
so much harder than breaking up.

37:37.830 --> 37:40.448
There's just
a really big difference

37:40.466 --> 37:43.918
between marrying a person

37:43.952 --> 37:46.137
and marrying an idea.

37:46.171 --> 37:47.505
What if he meets someone else?

37:47.556 --> 37:49.173
You think you two were meant to be?
Yes.

37:49.224 --> 37:51.459
Do you think you two
have a true love? Yes!

37:51.477 --> 37:52.844
Then stop worrying.

37:55.397 --> 37:57.348
I got to go.

37:57.399 --> 37:59.800
Thanks for the pin.
Sure.

37:59.818 --> 38:02.303
Hey...

38:02.321 --> 38:04.572
it's gonna be okay.

38:06.492 --> 38:08.359
How do you know that, though?

38:08.410 --> 38:12.530
When two people love each other
like you two do...

38:13.749 --> 38:15.583
...everything works out.

38:27.394 --> 38:29.028
Yes.

38:29.062 --> 38:30.363
All right, let's review.

38:30.397 --> 38:31.614
What are y'all gonna
do at regionals?

38:31.665 --> 38:33.032
Riff, run and grunt!

38:33.066 --> 38:34.450
Emote!
Commit!

38:34.501 --> 38:36.202
Step up to the plate
and embrace our talent.

38:36.236 --> 38:38.454
And just like my boo
Miss Mercedes Jones,

38:38.505 --> 38:40.290
we're gonna treat
every note we sing

38:40.341 --> 38:41.841
and every breath we take

38:41.875 --> 38:43.126
with a little
something-something

38:43.177 --> 38:45.345
we in the business of show
simply call "passion."

38:45.379 --> 38:46.679
And passion can be

38:46.714 --> 38:48.464
a scary thing,
but we shouldn't run

38:48.515 --> 38:49.882
or hide from it because

38:49.916 --> 38:51.884
passion is...
it's wonderful, yo.

38:51.918 --> 38:54.053
Auditorium,
4:00 p.m. sharp.

38:54.087 --> 38:56.055
I got a little jam
I'm gonna sing for all y'alls!

38:56.089 --> 38:58.741
And you best believe it's gonna
be sung with... say what?!

38:58.792 --> 39:00.743
Passion!

39:00.794 --> 39:02.078
Yes!
Thank you.

39:02.129 --> 39:04.030
Yes!

39:09.586 --> 39:11.421
What's that?

39:11.472 --> 39:12.755
It's a gift.

39:12.806 --> 39:14.724
I got it at the
Broadway Flea Market.

39:14.758 --> 39:19.429
It is Debbie Allen's original
cane from <i>Fame...</i> the movie.

39:19.463 --> 39:22.065
Hmm. I wanted to thank
you for what you did.

39:22.099 --> 39:23.049
The number?

39:23.067 --> 39:24.434
That's NYADA tradition.

39:24.485 --> 39:27.620
We do that when one of the tribe
gets a Broadway audition.

39:27.655 --> 39:29.939
Not the number.
I wanted to

39:29.990 --> 39:32.108
thank you for everything that
you've done for me this year.

39:32.159 --> 39:34.110
So... thank you.

39:34.161 --> 39:36.112
I've busted your ass
since September.

39:36.163 --> 39:37.229
You made me a better dancer.

39:37.247 --> 39:39.231
And that's why I came to NYADA,

39:39.249 --> 39:41.084
to learn and be challenged,

39:41.118 --> 39:43.753
and to work with the
best of the best.

39:43.787 --> 39:45.738
I saw something in you.

39:45.756 --> 39:48.741
That first day,
and I thought to myself,

39:48.759 --> 39:50.460
"This one's special.

39:50.511 --> 39:52.411
This one might make it."

39:52.429 --> 39:54.931
And that's why
I'm so relentless.

39:56.433 --> 39:58.918
Even the whole Brody thing?

39:58.936 --> 40:01.637
Well, that was
because of his abs.

40:01.689 --> 40:03.306
What? But yours are
so much better.

40:03.357 --> 40:04.590
When's your callback?

40:04.608 --> 40:06.526
Oh, it's next week.

40:07.361 --> 40:09.145
I am so nervous, Miss July.

40:09.196 --> 40:11.597
